description.narrative: (Malawi): Health Communication for Life (HC4L) activity provides technical assistance to design and implement social and behavior change strategies to increase positive, healthy behaviors among Malawians. The activity enables the Government of Malawi (GoM) to lead national social behavior change communication (SBCC) programming and serves to coordinate key USAID implementing partners in support of national efforts. In close coordination with the GoM, HC4L conducts key health communication interventions to increase positive, healthy behaviors to combat malaria and improve maternal, neonatal, and child health (MNCH); family planning and reproductive health (FP/RH); nutrition; and water, sanitation and hygiene (WASH) practices. .Working with the Ministry of Health and Population, partners, and communities, the activity will target socio-cultural practices that impede adoption of good health-seeking practices and behaviors using multi-channel SBCC initiatives including capacity development of GoM staff. The Activity will scale up development of effective, locally-adapted and evidence-based social and behavior change interventions to reach poor, marginalized and vulnerable people to prevent diseases and foster positive health practices. In addition, HC4L promotes open dialogue on gender dynamics among adolescents and mothers and champions male involvement. .By increasing health-seeking behaviors, HC4L will directly support the accomplishment of President's Malaria Initiative objectives and the Integrated Country Strategy objective 1.1 social development improved, most notably sub-objective 1.1.3: "Promote gender equality in development initiatives to increase girls' participation in education and improved health decision-making."......
